### EV Owner Management API Tests

### 1. Login as Backoffice User (for admin operations)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@evstation.com",
  "password": "Admin123!"
}

### 2. Create EV Owner (Backoffice only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/evowners
Authorization: Bearer {{backofficeToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "nic": "123456789V",
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "phone": "+94771234567",
  "password": "EVOwner123!",
  "isActive": true
}

### 3. Get All EV Owners (Backoffice only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/evowners
Authorization: Bearer {{backofficeToken}}

### 4. Get EV Owner by NIC (Backoffice only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/evowners/123456789V
Authorization: Bearer {{backofficeToken}}

### 5. Search EV Owners (Backoffice only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/evowners/search?query=John
Authorization: Bearer {{backofficeToken}}

### 6. Update EV Owner (Backoffice only)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/evowners/123456789V
Authorization: Bearer {{backofficeToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "email": "john.doe.updated@example.com",
  "phone": "+94771234567",
  "password": "NewPassword123!",
  "isActive": true
}

### 7. Toggle EV Owner Active Status (Backoffice only)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/evowners/123456789V/toggle-active
Authorization: Bearer {{backofficeToken}}

### 8. EV Owner Login (Mobile App)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/evowner-login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "nic": "123456789V",
  "password": "EVOwner123!"
}

### 9. Delete EV Owner (Backoffice only)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/evowners/123456789V
Authorization: Bearer {{backofficeToken}}

### Variables
@baseUrl = https://localhost:7000
@backofficeToken = YOUR_BACKOFFICE_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
@evOwnerToken = YOUR_EV_OWNER_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
